templates.content:
This agreement outlines the terms and conditions for drone-based aerial photography and videography services provided by Recluma Creative Media.

‚∏ª

1. Scope of Work

Recluma will provide professional aerial content services using drones for photography, videography, or a combination of both. The service includes:
	‚Ä¢	Aerial footage and/or photographs captured using professional-grade drones
	‚Ä¢	Basic editing, color correction, and formatting
	‚Ä¢	Delivery of final files in high-resolution digital formats via online transfer
	‚Ä¢	All flights operated by licensed drone professionals under safety-compliant protocols

‚∏ª

2. Service Duration
	‚Ä¢	Half-Day Shoot: Up to 4 hours on location, including setup and flight time
	‚Ä¢	Full-Day Shoot: Up to 8 hours on location, including setup, breaks, and multiple flights if required

‚∏ª

3. Deliverables

The deliverables may include one or more of the following depending on the project scope:
	‚Ä¢	Edited aerial photographs in JPEG and/or RAW formats
	‚Ä¢	Edited aerial video clips in HD or 4K resolution
	‚Ä¢	Files delivered within 5 to 7 working days after the shoot unless otherwise agreed
	‚Ä¢	Optional enhancements (e.g., music, graphics, storytelling) may be arranged separately

‚∏ª

4. Payment Terms
	‚Ä¢	A 50% deposit is required upon confirmation of the booking to reserve the shoot date
	‚Ä¢	The remaining 50% balance is due upon delivery of the final content
	‚Ä¢	Payments can be made via bank transfer, credit card, or mobile money
	‚Ä¢	No materials will be released until the final payment is received

‚∏ª

5. Transportation Costs

Transportation to and from the shooting location is charged separately and added to the final invoice. This includes any required boat transfers, fuel, or vehicle rentals necessary for access to the site.

‚∏ª

6. Client Responsibilities
	‚Ä¢	The client must provide appropriate access and permissions to the property or location
	‚Ä¢	If permits are required for flying or filming, the client must secure them in advance unless otherwise arranged with Recluma
	‚Ä¢	The client should inform Recluma of any local restrictions or limitations regarding drone use

‚∏ª

7. Rescheduling & Cancellations
	‚Ä¢	Rescheduling is allowed free of charge if done at least 48 hours in advance
	‚Ä¢	Cancellations made within 48 hours of the scheduled shoot may incur a cancellation fee
	‚Ä¢	If weather conditions make flying unsafe, the shoot may be rescheduled at no extra charge
	‚Ä¢	Deposits are non-refundable in cases of late cancellation without valid cause

‚∏ª

8. Usage Rights
	‚Ä¢	The client receives full usage rights for all delivered content for commercial, marketing, or internal purposes
	‚Ä¢	Recluma retains the right to use the material for its own promotional purposes (portfolio, website, social media), unless the client explicitly requests otherwise in writing

‚∏ª

9. Liability Disclaimer

Recluma is not liable for any restrictions imposed by local authorities, property owners, or environmental conditions that prevent the execution of the planned drone shoot. All equipment is operated by trained professionals following local aviation and safety laws.

modelAgreements.title: Cast & Modeling Agreement
modelAgreements.content:
FASHION CAST AGENCY

Comprehensive Model Registration & Collaboration Agreement (Non-Exclusive)

This agreement is made between Fashion Cast Agency (‚ÄúFCA‚Äù) and the individual signing below (‚Äúthe Model‚Äù). It outlines how the collaboration works, how content is produced and used, and what rights and responsibilities apply to both parties.

‚∏ª

1. Purpose and Overview

FCA helps build your professional presence and connects you with fashion brands, designers, lifestyle companies, and creative teams. We invest in photography, video, and AI-generated visuals to showcase your creative potential.

This is a non-exclusive agreement. The Model may freely work with other agencies or accept independent jobs at any time.

‚∏ª

2. How Our Process Works

2.1 Registration and Promotion

After signing, FCA creates promotional visuals for the Model, including photos, AI-generated composites, and short videos. These are produced at FCA‚Äôs expense and used to introduce the Model to potential clients.

The Model is not tied exclusively to FCA and may collaborate with others.

2.2 Brand Engagement

When a brand shows interest, FCA contacts the Model with full project details. No project begins without the Model‚Äôs explicit approval.

2.3 Concept Development

Once the Model and brand agree to proceed, FCA produces draft visuals to preview the collaboration. Final production begins only after both sides fully approve the concept.

2.4 Final Production

FCA produces final campaign visuals and delivers them for approval. Once approved, the content is published on FCA‚Äôs platforms and/or the brand‚Äôs platforms.

All approvals are final.

‚∏ª

3. Payment and Commission

FCA does not charge the Model for promotional visuals.
For paid brand campaigns, FCA receives a commission between 15%‚Äì20%, depending on the project.

‚∏ª

4. Booking Rules

FCA proposes only jobs that match the Model‚Äôs personality, comfort level, and goals.
The Model may decline any job. FCA never books the Model without approval.

‚∏ª

5. Image Usage Rights and Ownership

Once the Model approves final campaign visuals, the Model grants FCA and the brand the permanent right to use that content for:
	‚Ä¢	social media
	‚Ä¢	websites
	‚Ä¢	promotional materials
	‚Ä¢	online advertising
	‚Ä¢	lookbooks and digital campaigns

The Model still owns their personal likeness, but the specific approved visuals become permanently licensed and cannot be revoked.

Approved and published content can never be removed unless FCA chooses to do so voluntarily.

‚∏ª

6. Contract Duration and Termination

This agreement is valid for five (5) years from the date of signing.

Either party may terminate the agreement with 30 days‚Äô written notice.

Termination does not affect any approved and published content; such content remains permanently in FCA‚Äôs archive.

‚∏ª

7. Content Permanence and AI Training

All approved visuals may be used permanently by FCA and collaborating brands.
The content may also be used to train FCA‚Äôs AI systems and to generate new promotional materials.

Published content cannot be edited, restricted, removed, or deleted by the Model.

Only FCA has the right to decide whether content remains online.

‚∏ª

8. Penalty for Leaving the Agency Within First Two Years

The Model is always free to leave FCA.
However, if the Model decides to terminate their membership and leave FCA within the first two (2) years of this agreement, the Model agrees to pay a contractual exit penalty of 900 USD.

This penalty compensates FCA for:
	‚Ä¢	portfolio creation
	‚Ä¢	AI training value
	‚Ä¢	promotional investment
	‚Ä¢	brand development work
	‚Ä¢	content production costs

This penalty applies ONLY if the Model chooses to leave FCA within the first 2 years.
It does NOT apply for reporting, blocking, or removing content ‚Äî because content cannot be removed under any circumstance.

After two years, there is no financial penalty for leaving the agency.

‚∏ª

9. Confidentiality

The Model agrees to keep all unreleased campaigns and brand communication confidential until publicly released. FCA will protect the Model‚Äôs data securely and respectfully.

‚∏ª

10. Governing Law

This agreement is governed by the laws of the United Republic of Tanzania.

Any disputes will be resolved first through negotiation, then through arbitration or court proceedings in Tanzania if necessary.

‚∏ª

PROJECT PARTICIPATION AGREEMENT

This Project Participation Agreement ("Agreement") is entered into as of 12/4/2025 between:

AGENCY: Fashion Cast Agency 
Address: No: 47 B - 2601 Folkart Towers  Symirna Tr. 

Email: info@fashioncast.agency

MODEL/TALENT: Kalo
Email: Georgiev.kalojan@gmail.com

PROJECT DETAILS:

Project Name: THE NEST HOLIDAY
Company/Brand: THE NEST 
Usage Platforms: Instagram, TikTok
Content Type: AI-Generated Content

PROJECT DESCRIPTION:
TEST 

TERMS AND CONDITIONS:

1. PERMANENT USAGE RIGHTS
The Model hereby grants THE NEST  and Fashion Cast Agency  perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide rights to use, reproduce, modify, publish, and distribute all content (including but not limited to photographs, videos, images, and AI-generated content) created for this project.

2. SCOPE OF USAGE
The content may be used on the following platforms and media: Instagram, TikTok

3. IRREVOCABILITY
These rights are PERMANENT and CANNOT BE REVOKED once this agreement is signed. The Model acknowledges and agrees that:
